      <hedline>
        <hl1>Sartorial Sipowicz</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jennifer M Farley letter says there is no such thing as a short-sleeved dress shirt for men, and wearing one might be dubbed 'doing a Sipowicz' (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To Sunday Styles:</p>
        <p>It is my belief that there is no such thing as a short-sleeved dress shirt (''For Corporate Rebels, Short-Sleeved Shirts,'' June 21), even with a tie. My son and his friends, New Yorkers, call it ''doing a Sipowicz.''</p>
        <p>JENNIFER M. FARLEY  Darien, Conn.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
